We ordered food and it took an hour for them to make half of our meal. The food here is good. Our waitress never smiled, or apologized after she gave us the wrong drinks two times. We were in a hurry to get to another town and the other half of our order was taking over an hour so we called it done, and told them to just cancel the rest. They gave us our total and we ended up paying for the orders that never got brought out for us. Later they took off our tax, so our price went down by a little. I’m not saying we are cheap. But if the food in a restaurant is really really good, we will be willing to pay a good amount of money. This restaurant has a decent quality service. I honestly think they were messing with us since they could tell we weren’t from Brooklyn, yet only on vacation and stopping in. Also the first time that I’ve ever came across a waitress losing our order ticket. If you are visiting here I recommend to not come to this place. They like to think they can trick us just because we aren’t from Brooklyn.

I came for a visit in New York and this was near where I stayed so despite the bad reviews I still decide to give it a try. I went for lunch time with my brother for the advertised all you can eat lunch buffet for $13.99 and it was 3:30 so as our order was being made, I checked the time and it was 3:50 before our first sushi order came out. Let me just add that the atmosphere was awkward because the girl and the sushi chefs stares you down when you eat and judges you high-key based on the UNBELIEVABLE amount of food you ordered. This is the first time I had felt so umcomfortable at a restaurant and I try to be understanding because I am a server myself. The second order of rolls that came out later was made after 4:00 because they were hesitant on if we can finish what we ordered which was the end of the lunch buffet but keep in mind that we ordered everything before dinner buffet. As I went up to pay, the girl upfront said if you pay with cash you get $3 off but I was sure that applied only for dinner so she wanted to charge me almost $40 for the dinner buffet because the rolls were "ordered and made" past 4:00 but I explained nicely to her that we ordered at lunch time so she charged me a total of $25 for the lunch that I came for and said sarcastically the $3 off won't be included because it only applies for dinner buffet, girl no thank you, I much rather take the lunch that I came for. So, please watch your time when you come in to eat for their buffet and false advertisement and  your checks. Beyond dissappointed.

I usually go for a bento box at Japanese restaurants. I asked for substitutions instead of the usual California roll and shumai, but they told me no substitutions because it's more work for the sushi chef. I told her that she could charge me extra and she very reluctantly agreed and said that she would only allow it this 1 time. It was not busy when I went...so, they clearly put their own convenience before their customers' needs. I guess "客户就是上帝" does not apply here.  Another disappointment was that they don't have the mild dark tempura sauce that most restaurants give.  The main pro about this place is that it is 50% off for takeout. This makes their takeout price nearly unbeatable.  Every time I go, I only see young sushi chefs and young cashier/waitresses. I never see the owner around. I feel like the owner should be around to manage his employees.

(Translated by Google) The decoration is individual, it looks clean and hygienic, the light is bright, the individual music is played, and the waiters are polite. The format of the buffet is free to order some common ones, perhaps the simplest to show the real skill of the sushi chef. Udon soup is sweet and sour in the mouth. It is nostalgic for Cantonese sauerkraut soup. Of course, it is not sauerkraut soup. Crab meat salad looks good. Cut the crab fillet and cucumber into thin slices. The taste is sweet and sour, which is the flavor of the salad, followed by the crispness of cucumber, and the texture of crab shreds like gluten. Only then did I feel the bitterness accumulated from cucumber, and the salad became the protagonist of this dish. For deep-fried shrimps, the shrimps are shelled and then fried in a batter. When serving, they are topped with sour plum sauce, which is crispy in the mouth, sweet and sour from the plum sauce, and then to the taste of shrimp. Perhaps this form of expression is the taste of the people in this place.  (Original) 装修个性，看上去干净卫生 ，光线明亮，播放个性音乐，服务员有礼貌。 自助餐的形式，随意要一些常见的，或许最简单才显出寿司师的真功夫。 乌冬汤，入口酸甜，有一种粤菜酸菜汤的怀念，当然它不是酸菜汤。 蟹肉沙拉，看上去刀功还可以，将蟹柳和青瓜均匀切丝，入口酸甜，是沙拉的味道 ，其次是青瓜的爽脆，再是蟹丝像面筋一样的口感，到最后才感觉到青瓜积累下来的苦涩味，沙拉成为这道菜的主角。 炸虾，将虾去壳后再上糊酥炸，上盘时再淋上酸梅子酱，入口酥脆，再梅子酱的酸甜，再到虾肉的味道，酥脆成为这道菜的特色。 或许是这种表达形式才是这地方人们的味道。
